<subSubSection id="C3046513FFDFFFDCFEDAA7882A7EAC44" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA13698FFDFFFDCFEDAA7882A7EAC44" blockId="24.[264,1323,284,790]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="B96AEA8AFFDFFFDCFEDAA7882FC9AD97" box="[312,414,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Remarks</emphasis>
: This is the largest among the species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D1BFFDFFFDCFC62A7882DADAD97" box="[896,1018,684,709]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96AEA8AFFDFFFDCFC62A7882DADAD97" box="[896,1018,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Xenovarta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and can be easily recognised by the basal processes to the aedeagus. It shares the opening of the gonopore at midlength of shaft with H. 
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D1BFFDFFFDCFDA7A7D82C96AC47" box="[581,705,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="compressa">
<emphasis id="B96AEA8AFFDFFFDCFDA7A7D82C96AC47" box="[581,705,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">compressa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but only distantly related to it.
</paragraph>
